html^(<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <title>O computed plot</title>
  <style>
    body { font-family: system-ui, sans-serif; max-width: 780px; margin: 3em auto; }
    img  { max-width: 100%; border: 1px solid #ddd; border-radius: 8px; }
    figcaption { color: #666; font-size: 0.9em; margin-top: 0.5em; }
    code { background: #f4f4f4; padding: 1px 5px; border-radius: 3px; }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
<h1>An O-lang report with live Python</h1>
<p>
  The figure below was produced by Python code embedded in this HTML document.
  The Python block ran inside env <code>python[0]</code> and returned a matplotlib
  Figure, which the HTML backend automatically rendered as a <code>&lt;img&gt;</code>
  data-URL.
</p>
<figure>
python[0]{cap=backend,fs_read,fs_write,network,process}^(
import matplotlib
matplotlib.use("Agg")
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import math

fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(6.5, 3.6))
xs = [i / 40 for i in range(-400, 400)]
ax.plot(xs, [math.sin(x) for x in xs], label="sin x")
ax.plot(xs, [math.sin(x) * math.exp(-x*x/40) for x in xs], label="sin x . exp(-x^2/40)")
ax.axhline(0, color="#888", linewidth=0.5)
ax.set_xlabel("x")
ax.set_ylabel("y")
ax.set_title("Two curves computed at render time")
ax.legend()
fig
)_python[0]{cap=backend,fs_read,fs_write,network,process}
<figcaption>Figure 1. Computed at render time, embedded via OBlob(mime="image/png").</figcaption>
</figure>
<p>
  The first ten values of a sequence computed in the SAME python[0] environment
  (note <code>math</code> is still imported from the previous block):
</p>
<p>python[0]{cap=backend,fs_read,fs_write,network,process}^([round(math.sin(i/3), 3) for i in range(10)])_python[0]{cap=backend,fs_read,fs_write,network,process}</p>
<p>
  And a completely separate env <code>python[1]</code> that doesn't share
  state with <code>python[0]</code>:
</p>
<p>python[1]^(
    try:
        math   # should raise NameError -- python[1] never imported math
        answer = "math is defined"
    except NameError:
        answer = "math is NOT defined in python[1]"
    answer
)_python[1]</p>
</body>
</html>
